nodes.bodyText: So compatibility requires a perfect match?

I've just looked at a proposed PR that replaces TR::Compiler->target.cpu.id() >= TR_PPCp7; with TR::Compiler->target.cpu.isAtLeast(TR_PPCp7);
This PR seems to be doing the opposite
Do we have comp() object somewhere handy so that we can avoid the TLS lookup?
These asserts will go away as far I understand, so we could replace them with TR_ASSERT_FATAL without worrying about extra overhead forever.
I see that we have comp already available, so cg->comp() could be replaced by comp
